<h2>Get started</h2> 

<pre>
================
Ptah dev example
================

1. Create dir `ptah`

  >> mkdir ptah
  >> cd ptah

2. Init git repo:

  >> git init
  >> git remote add origin git://github.com/ptahproject/devel.git
  >> git fetch origin
  >> git merge origin/master

3.run buildout, python2.7.2 is required:

   >> python2.7 ./bootstrap.py
   >> ./bin/buildout -N -c readonly.cfg

4. Run application:

   >> ./bin/paster serve ptah.ini

5. Application runs on 8080 port:

   >> http://localhost:8080/

5. Default login `admin`, password: `12345`

6. List application settings

   >> ./bin/paster settings -a
   >> ./bin/paster settings -l mail
   >> ./bin/paster settings -p

7. Application template customizations

   >> ./bin/paster templates -h

8. Application static assets management

  >> ./bin/paster static -h

</pre>
